<HEADLINE>
AT LEAST WIVES ARE GETTING ALONG
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ There may be some hard feelings between UCLA coach
Bob Toledo and USC coach Paul Hackett, but the same apparently does
not apply to their wives.
</P>
<P>
   Elizabeth Hackett and Elaine Toledo hugged and exchanged a kiss
between the locker rooms after USC's 17-7 victory over UCLA on
Saturday at the Coliseum.
</P>
<P>
   As for their husbands, Paul Hackett admitted after the game that
he had been upset at Bob Toledo following last season's Bruins
victory.
</P>
<P>
   ``I felt a little animosity a year ago. I had not been in this
game for a while,'' Hackett said. ``I came out of the game a little
angry, only because I hadn't experienced it.
</P>
<P>
   ``As I look back, Bob was acting like he should. He had his game
face on and I was probably overreacting.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett was mad that Toledo had Cade McNown fake a run and try a
bootleg in the final 23 seconds of last year's game.
</P>
<P>
   Asked if he thought about having quarterback John Fox roll out
in the final minute, Hackett only laughed.
</P>
<P>
   The best? Hackett was asked if this was the biggest victory of
his career?
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought the win in Hawaii was pretty big,'' he joked. ``This
is bigger.''
</P>
<P>
   Where's Soward? Wide receiver R. Jay Soward caught just three
passes for 35 yards, but for a while it looked like he would have
only one catch.
</P>
<P>
   Soward, who said he was not bothered by his strained left
hamstring, fumbled on his first reception in the first quarter, and
did not play the rest of the half.
</P>
<P>
   ``The coaches, you know, felt after the fumble that maybe I'm
not ready after not practicing all week,'' Soward said. ``I came
back and I turned third downs into first downs in the second half.
I was a role player and if that was my role, I'll do it.''
</P>
<P>
   Steele out? Linebacker Markus Steele has torn tissue on the side
of his hip said there was a 50-50 chance he would play this week
against Louisiana Tech.
</P>
<P>
   Cookie time: Fox said the best thing about beating UCLA would be
going to his favorite cookie store in Westwood.
</P>
<P>
   ``They make my favorite chocolate-chip cookies and it's been
pretty tough going over there,'' Fox said. ``You had to kind of
hang your head low before. Now, I think I'll have to go get some
cookies.''
</P>
<P>
   The workhorse: Tailback Chad Morton had a career-high 36 carries
for 143 yards. It was the most carries by a Trojan since Steven
Webster had 40 carries against Washington State in 1987. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
