<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCLA-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NO RUNNING ROOM FOR FOSTER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ A year ago, after rushing for 109 yards and
scoring four touchdowns, he was UCLA's hero. Saturday, after his
fourth-quarter fumble cost the Bruins a potential touchdown,
sophomore tailback DeShaun Foster felt an eight-game winning streak
collapse on his sturdy shoulders.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is pretty much (as low) as I've been,'' he said. ``I'm
upset with myself. It was a key situation and a key spot on the
field.''
</P>
<P>
   No one faulted Foster's effort. Running behind a makeshift line
and facing a ferocious USC defense, Foster rushed 17 times for 59
yards. They were tough yards, agonizing yards. Only once, on a
23-yard bolt, did he have room to roam.
</P>
<P>
   Even the fumble came after 2 bruising yards into the heart of
USC's defense, and in that respect it reflected UCLA's afternoon.
Their dominance of the running game ended at eight games, as well.
</P>
<P>
   They rushed for 45 yards.
</P>
<P>
   USC rushed for 214.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had a hard time sustaining drives and running the
football,'' Bruins coach Bob Toledo said.
</P>
<P>
   Not great, not bad: In his first career start, freshman
quarterback Ryan McCann completed 17 of 29 passes for 204 yards and
three interceptions.
</P>
<P>
   Toledo's assessment: ``He was spotty. He made some nice plays
and some bad ones. But he'll get better. He'll learn from it.''
</P>
<P>
   Trick's on U-CLA: The Bruins tried four trick plays: a reverse
to Foster, a fake receiver pass, a hook-and-ladder, and their first
fake field goal in years.
</P>
<P>
   None of it worked, and the fake field goal cost them
holder/safety Joey Strycula, who sprained his ankle on the run and
missed several series in the second quarter.
</P>
<P>
   ``My concern was that we would have a hard time scoring,''
Toledo said. ``That (fake) was a way to keep the drive alive.''
</P>
<P>
   Odds and ends: The loss was Toledo's first in the city series.
He was 3-0 as a USC assistant in the 1970s, 2-0 as UCLA's offensive
coordinator in 1994-95 and 3-0 as the Bruins' coach....
</P>
<P>
   Third-down defense doomed UCLA again: USC completed 9 of 22
attempts....
</P>
<P>
   McCann was sacked six times....
</P>
<P>
   Linebacker Ryan Nece led the Bruins with 10 tackles. Defensive
end Kenyon Coleman, who played one of his best games, had nine....
</P>
<P>
   Toledo on Stanford winning the Pac-10 title: ``I called (coach
Tyrone Willingham) this week and wished him luck. I was hoping
they'd win. He's very deserving. And they'll be good. But they've
got to stop that Mack truck. (Wisconsin running back Ron Dayne) is
a heck of a runner.''...
</P>
<P>
   UCLA opens the 2000 season Sept. 2 in the Rose Bowl, against
Alabama. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
