the time Clinton leaves office.
</P>
<P>
   ``You've just got to grind it out,'' Leavy said, ``and have the
long-term vision that Russia's transition is probably the single
most important foreign policy challenge long term.''
</P>
<P>
   (EDs: Story can end here. Optional add follows.)
</P>
<P>
   Similarly, the global trading order won't be built in a day.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton hopes for advances in the negotiating round set to begin
in Seattle Nov. 30 for the WTO, the Geneva-based group that sets
the rules and regulations for global commerce. That round is likely
to take three years to conclude, however, long after Clinton has
