<HEADLINE>
TREASURY SCHEDULES BILL AND NOTE SALES 
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds: The word PLUS in parentheses has been used twice instead of
the symbol, which is non-transmittable to many newspaper systems.) 
(lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financing this week includes Monday's
regular weekly auction of new three- and six-month bills and a
two-year note being auctioned Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   At the close of the New York cash market on Friday, traders
said, the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was 5.06 percent
and a six-month bill was 5.20 percent. In when-issued trading, the
two-year note was offered at a price to yield 5.89 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The following taxable and tax-exempt fixed-income issues are
scheduled for pricing this week:
</P>
<P>
   TAXABLE
</P>
<P>
   ONE DAY DURING THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   Federal Realty Investment Trust, $150 million notes due 2009,
Baa2/BBB(PLUS)/---. Goldman, Sachs &AMP; Co. and J.P. Morgan
Securities.
</P>
<P>
   Niagara Mohawk Power Corp., 3 million shares of $50 fixed
adjustable rate cumulative preferred stock (FRAPS),
Ba1/BB(PLUS)/---. Salomon Smith Barney.
</P>
<P>
   Sandy Spring Capital Trust I, 1.4 million shares of $25
cumulative trust preferred. ---/---/---. Legg Mason Wood Walker
Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Source: MCM CorporateWatch
</P>
<P>
   Ratings: Moody's Investors Service/Standard &AMP; Poor's Corp./Duff
&AMP; Phelps Credit.
</P>
<P>
   TAX EXEMPT
</P>
<P>
   ONE DAY DURING THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   Alaska Housing, $104 million of state capital project bonds.
George K. Baum &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Mountain State Health Alliance Health &AMP; Education Facility of
the City of Johnson City, Tenn., $445 million of debt securities.
Lehman Brothers.
</P>
<P>
   Pennsylvania Housing Finance Authority, $75 million of single
family revenue bonds. PaineWebber Inc.
</P>
