Nov. 22 and thereafter. For questions about stories, please call
(818) 713-3705.
</P>
<P>
   LAUSD-FAKE-MONEY (Los Angeles) -- Thousands of dollars in
counterfeit money is passing hands in Los Angeles school cafeterias
and book stores, according to Don Mullinax, the district's top
auditor and investigator. ``It's an easy way to launder money,''
Mullinax said. ``A student uses a fake $20 bill to buy a candy bar
and comes away with $19 that are `clean.' They can then use that
real money on the street.'' Mullinax and secret service agents will
speak at Eagle Rock High School this week. By Greg Gittrich. Will
move on the ``n'' California news wire and ``a'' national wire.
</P>
