Will move on the ``n'' California news wire and ``a'' National
wire.
</P>
<P>
   LAPD-TRADEMARK (Los Angeles) -- To protect and to serve -- and
profit. Whether you cherish or dislike the Los Angeles Police
Department, officials believe the global reputation of L.A's Finest
is worth millions -- and a new business venture: trademarking the
LAPD. If policymakers approve this unique new proposal, film and
television productions using the Department's symbols -- like
badges, logos, patches and the Department seal -- will be shelling
out cash to do so. And retailers selling LAPD hats, shirts, coffee
mugs and model squad cars also would pay a license fee or face
being sued. By Phillip W. Browne. Will move on the ``n'' California
news wire and ``a'' national wire.
</P>
