<SLUG> BC-BKC-USCPRE-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NATION TO SEE USC VS. NORTH CAROLINA
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC will probably play bigger basketball games
this season, but none will receive the national exposure of
tonight's game against fifth-ranked North Carolina in the Maui
Invitational.
</P>
<P>
   The game will be televised by ESPN and give the Trojans (1-0)
one of their largest audiences in several years.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can't get better exposure than that,'' USC coach Henry
Bibby said. ``We're out there to get better as a team. Obviously
we'll see where the program is. But it will give us more recruiting
and national exposure for USC than in a long time.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans have played marquee schools in recent years, with
games against Kansas the past two seasons, and North Carolina in
1996, but none of those contests were nationally televised.
</P>
<P>
   It's probably the biggest game from a national standpoint since
USC played ninth-ranked Cincinnati at the Sports Arena on Super
Bowl Sunday in 1997 on ABC. USC lost to the Bearcats 100-81.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-11-21-99 2136EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
