respectable report card, with plenty of A's, when the House
subcommittee tracking Year 2000 preparations issues what it calls
its final grades. But one reason things look so rosy is that the
subcommittee has decided not to issue grades for more than 40 vital
government programs, including Medicaid and Medicare. By Barnaby J.
Feder.
